            <bug_when>2009-11-16 10:56:56 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>It is a common scenario that a dialog has more than one select box for example. But in most of the cases, the user does not manipulate the select box at all so he does not need the ListItems in the select boxes list. 
So for better performance it would be nice to create the ListItems not the moment the target is bound. A better approach is to create the widgets right before they are needed.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>14151</commentid>
            <who name="Martin Wittemann">martin.wittemann</who>
            <bug_when>2009-11-17 14:37:13 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>After further evaluation I figured out that the ListItems are necessary even if the list has not been opened. So a lazy creation of the ListItems is not a quick task and we can wait until we have virtual widgets which handle all these problems.</thetext>
